{
  "texts": [
    "Third, peaks are broadened using the Scherrer equation to mimic the effects of small particle size, including grain sizes between 5 and 30 nm.",
    "Fourth, impurity peaks are added at randomly selected positions (2θ) with intensities as large as 50% of the maximum pattern intensity.",
    "Based on these artifacts, we generate a total of 200 augmented patterns for each phase that are then used for model training.",
    "Further details regarding these augmentations can be found in previous work 19.",
    "For the simulation of test data used to evaluate our method's performance, we used broader limits on the magnitude of each artifact."
  ]
}